headline: Consumer sentiment, Regeneron meeting, Apple WWDC: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton preview the top market stories and headlines Wall Street will be paying attention to tomorrow, Friday, June 13, including June's preliminary consumer sentiment reading, Regeneron Pharmaceuticals' (REGN) annual shareholder meeting, and the closing day of Apple's (AAPL) 2025 Worldwide Developers Conference (WWDC). To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.

headline: Is This Stock a Buy After Acquiring a Potential Zepbound Competitor?
summary: Regeneron acquired a promising weight management asset that could become lucrative.  Shares of Regeneron (NASDAQ: REGN) have declined this year due to issues with one of its former growth drivers, Eylea, a medicine that treats wet age-related macular degeneration.  Is Regeneron stock a buy now?
